❤️ G I V E A W A Y ❤️

I just made a Twitter account! To incentivize quick growth and promote the debut of Jadu’s AR Mirrorverse we are choosing one participant to win Meebit #9071 currently worth $10,000…

Rules to enter:⠀
1) Like this post⠀
2) Tag as many friends in the comments as possible. More comments = more entries!⠀
3) Follow trippylabs & jaduhologram on Twitter (Links in bio) 
4 ) Join our Discords (Links in bio) 

That’s it!

The winner will be chosen randomly and announced in 2 days. 

Stay tuned for our upcoming Jetpack NFT Drop within the Mirrorverse!! 

Must be 13+ years old to enter.⠀
*This giveaway is not affiliated with Instagram*⠀

Good luck!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trippy on August 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'jaduhologram Meebits are 20,000 unique characters that have been generated by Larva Labs and registered on the blockchain. Among many new features, we 're happy to share, that Jadu 4.0 will be bringing Meebits to life in AR as playable characters! We've been humbled by your support over our year and a half of existence and have been able to grow our team steadily because of it. We're feeling more ambitious than ever before and have a long list of features in development right now that are about to take us well beyond musical holograms.'.

node.text: It is the individuals task to differentiate themselves from all the others and stand on their own feet. All collective identities interfere with the fulfillment of this task. Such identities are shields for the timid, beds for the lazy, and safe havens for the irresponsible.

node.text:
The first full-quality full-length NFT music video, “Claire,” by @anyma_ofc & @marigoldff is out today on @superrare.co 🔥 We utilized KSPEC, an open source museological grade protocol to expand the ERC-721 NFT standard. This groundbreaking technology allows for complex artworks, provenance, indefinite transparent preservation, and unlimited file sizes on chain. 

This is a watershed moment that sets precedent as the worlds of digital art, crypto and music intersect. With few exceptions, NFTs have been limited to a fixed file size <500MB, confining the length, fidelity, and creative scope of the work being sold. Meanwhile, music videos have been costly endeavors for artists, with music sales being the only option to recoup expenses. Now, these productions can be collected in full quality. We are witnessing the emergence of a new opportunity for artists to engage with NFTs as a vehicle to deliver art directly to collectors. A new renaissance without gatekeepers and industry intermediaries is unfolding.

I predict all NFTs will embrace this protocol in due time. Thanks to @alessiodevecchi & @kanondotart for helping bring this to life! 

I am thrilled, this is history!!

node.text: Ayahuasca is driven by sound, by song, by whistling. Its ability to transform sound, including vocal sound, into the visual spectrum indicates that some kind of information processing membrane or boundary is being overcome by the pharmacology of this stuff. Things normally experienced as acoustic become visibly beheld, and it's quite spectacular.
